      "severity": "MAJOR-REVISION",
      "justification": "If confirmed, this requires revision because the paper's main comparative conclusions depend on the chosen reference class. The author does acknowledge this, but the issue is deeper than a caveat: there is no demonstration that this null preserves the relevant nuisance structure of Koide-type statistics or corresponds to any scientifically defensible baseline for quark masses. Different priors materially change tail fractions, including the full-search result and several claim rankings. The findings may survive under some alternatives, but the current quantitative conclusions are not robustly grounded."
